      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0114">
               <p>Bastable, apparently a native of <placeName>Middlezoy, Somerset</placeName>, began
                  &apos;exhorting&apos; in <date when="1747">1747</date> and came to <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s attention as a
                  promising prospective preacher in <date when="1748-09">Sept. 1748</date>. He
                  appears in the Minutes as a &apos;probationary helper&apos; in <date when="1750"
                     >1750</date>, but did not advance to the regular <seg ana="itinerancy"
                     >itinerancy</seg>, likely because he married <persName>Catherine
                     Stockdale</persName> (<date from="1726" to="1786">1726–86</date>) in
                     <placeName>Cork</placeName> in <date when="1752">1752</date> (see <hi
                     rend="italic">Works</hi>, 10:205, 237). Their time thereafter was split between
                     <placeName>Cork</placeName> and <placeName>Bristol</placeName>. Bastable&apos;s
                  letters to <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> in <date
                     when="1767">1767</date> show him to be in failing health. He died in
                     <placeName>Bristol</placeName> in <date when="1775-06">June 1775</date>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
